<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1807,1977]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,724,1879,1905]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Record as epibiont on other hosts/substrata:</emphasis>
This species was found attached to a variety of substrates (
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. &amp; Paynter, J." pageId="15" pageNumber="166" pagination="17 - 59" refId="ref18853" refString="Warren, A. &amp; Paynter, J. (1991) A revision of Cothurnia (Ciliophora, Peritrichida) and its morphological relatives. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology, 57 (1), 17 - 59." type="journal article" year="1991">Warren &amp; Paynter 1991</bibRefCitation>
); recently was found on oligochaete 
<taxonomicName box="[796,973,1915,1942]" class="Clitellata" family="Naididae" genus="Tubificoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplotaxida" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[796,933,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Tubificoides</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from Bosporus Strait’s outlet area of the Black Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Sergeeva, N. &amp; Dovgal, I." box="[278,569,1951,1977]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref17547" refString="Sergeeva, N. &amp; Dovgal, I. (2014) First finding of epibiont peritrich and suctorian ciliates (Ciliophora) on oligochaetes and harpacticoid copepods from the deep-water hypoxic / anoxic conditions of the Black Sea. Ecologica Montenegrina, 1 (1), 49 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.37828 / em. 2014.1.7" type="journal article" year="2014">Sergeeva &amp; Dovgal 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
